Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.99,0:00:13.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The balls were really flowing today!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.47,0:00:15.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What a great haul!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.49,0:00:17.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.89,0:00:23.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll surprise Ran for always making fun of me for playing pachinko!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.53,0:00:25.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.95,0:00:28.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The pachinko king has returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.53,0:00:31.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.66,0:00:35.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.48,0:00:37.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.72,0:00:39.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm going to the hospital."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.80,0:00:42.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,"At least turn your phone on."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.82,0:00:43.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,"Ran."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.11,0:00:45.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,My phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.34,0:00:48.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops! It was off...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.57,0:00:54.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty-four missed calls\Nand sixteen messages?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.80,0:00:56.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.12,0:01:01.53,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mom wasn't feeling well at work,\Nand she's about to go into surgery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.53,0:01:04.32,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're are Haido Central\NHospital, so get here soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:05.17,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.21,0:01:09.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The hidden lines on the palm are the fuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.97,0:01:11.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The deduction catches fire on the line to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:13.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Running into Amuro at Central Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.81,0:01:16.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An incident occurs while four ladies are having tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.01,0:01:19.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the body of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.16,0:01:21.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.95,0:03:07.95,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)}The Tense Tea Party\N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.84,0:03:05.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Tense Tea Party, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.87,0:03:14.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.04,0:03:17.05,Hospital,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Haido Central Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.04,0:03:17.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:19.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.24,0:03:20.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.23,0:03:22.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.05,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Eri-sama
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:26.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Eri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.04,0:03:31.40,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you making so much noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.27,0:03:34.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.21,0:03:35.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You had surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.17,0:03:38.26,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,It was just appendicitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.26,0:03:42.57,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,The surgery ended a while ago. \NThe anesthesia wore off, and I just woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.15,0:03:46.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was just your appendix?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.30,0:03:47.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't "just" her appendix!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.77,0:03:49.95,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing with your phone off?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:54.79,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it was horses, mahjong, or pachinko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.79,0:03:57.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! I was working...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.34,0:03:58.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it pachinko?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.77,0:03:59.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.71,0:04:04.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Your jacket has a weird\Nwrinkle near your butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.73,0:04:05.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.45,0:04:09.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean you were sitting\Nin a chair for a long time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:11.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:15.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Also, your phone must have been off
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.55,0:04:17.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,because you were\Nsomewhere loud enough
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.07,0:04:20.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that you couldn't hear your phone ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.04,0:04:23.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't like to set your phone to vibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:24.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,because you think it's gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:28.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And look. Between your shoelaces...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:30.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You have a pachinko ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.83,0:04:34.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were definitely playing pachinko.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.65,0:04:38.03,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.62,0:04:41.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-I happened to see a mystery\Nshow just like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.86,0:04:43.42,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.75,0:04:47.80,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,You were captivated by pachinko\Nwhile I was having an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:48.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.82,0:04:56.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I-I just meant to go for a little while, but I was having such unusually good luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.72,0:05:02.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you should squeeze\None out so you can leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:06.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:09.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When you have appendix troubles, they say\Nyou can leave the hospital once you fart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:15.78,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you think you're being clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:20.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that was pretty\Ngood, if I say so myselfâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.13,0:05:23.99,DCMain,ERI,0000,0000,0000,,Get out, you hack detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:28.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.23,0:05:31.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I came because I was worried about her, and she's getting mad at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:33.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she's mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.45,0:05:34.52,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.11,0:05:38.19,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Mori-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.20,0:05:41.48,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.31,0:05:43.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bourbon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.91,0:05:45.88,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you not feeling well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.88,0:05:48.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.23,0:05:50.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.35,0:05:54.47,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's a member of the Black Organization\Ndoing at Haido Central Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.55,0:05:56.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.65,0:05:57.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:05:59.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.51,0:06:01.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.15,0:06:06.08,DCMain,AMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I heard one of my friends was\Nhospitalized and came to see him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.08,0:06:08.38,DCMain,AMURA,0000,0000,0000,,but he apparently disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.30,0:06:14.23,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,The nurses told me you'd been here before,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.23,0:06:15.46,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,so maybe you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.46,0:06:16.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.00,0:06:19.64,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,A man named Kusuda Rikumichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.17,0:06:22.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that? I don't know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.63,0:06:28.00,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I was hoping he'd return\Nthe money I lent him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.00,0:06:29.48,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you don't know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.48,0:06:30.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.79,0:06:33.20,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:34.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.27,0:06:38.05,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.36,0:06:41.63,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know a patient\Nnamed Kusuda Rikumichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:43.90,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kusuda Rikumichi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.88,0:06:47.10,Visitor,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Beppu Katsuki (41)\NVisitor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.39,0:06:45.41,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.41,0:06:46.55,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:47.30,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}How old is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.72,0:06:49.76,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Do you have a photo of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:49.76,Visitor2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Happo Tokie (42)\NVisitor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.53,0:06:52.50,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:53.79,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.75,0:06:57.65,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Mori-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.05,0:07:01.48,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do if someone suddenly\Nasked if you knew someone by name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:05.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'd probably respond\Nlike those ladies did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.08,0:07:07.09,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.09,0:07:11.61,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Most people don't have total\Nconfidence in their own memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.61,0:07:14.03,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why before answering no,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.03,0:07:18.16,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,they ask for information about\Nthe person besides their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.65,0:07:21.43,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you're amazing, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.26,0:07:26.36,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You knew he was a stranger\Nbased only on his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.26,0:07:30.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't take children so seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.00,0:07:34.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty of people will say they don't recognize\Nsomeone by name even when they've met.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.68,0:07:37.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Some people only know\Nothers by a nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.39,0:07:39.14,DCMain,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Three, two, one...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:40.48,DCMain,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,Zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.49,0:07:52.50,DCMain,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, the elevator's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.50,0:07:53.69,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:55.09,DCMain,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:57.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.18,0:07:59.37,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.82,0:08:03.17,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,My nickname is "Zero," so I\Nthought someone was calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.17,0:08:06.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why Zero? Isn't your name Toru?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:09.38,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Being transparent means\Nthere's nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.06,0:08:11.17,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Hence Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.61,0:08:15.89,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,That's how children come up with nicknames.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.34,0:08:22.06,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Kusuda Rikumichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.62,0:08:24.86,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,What about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.86,0:08:28.57,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone in the hallway\Njust asked if I knew him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.57,0:08:30.92,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I don't know him, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:34.79,Patient,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kosaka Juri (42)\NPatient
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.92,0:08:32.23,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I have a private room,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.23,0:08:36.07,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and I don't have many opportunities\Nto speak with other patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.24,0:08:38.15,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, great news!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:40.30,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you're getting out of\Nthe hospital tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.30,0:08:41.24,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.24,0:08:43.69,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,You should've told us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.69,0:08:46.08,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that make our visit meaningless?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.30,0:08:47.21,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:48.46,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Reina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.71,0:08:52.85,Visitor3,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Suto Reina (42)\NVisitor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.52,0:08:51.30,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You two came?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.30,0:08:53.01,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.34,0:08:55.35,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,I got some hot water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.35,0:08:56.86,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.86,0:09:01.01,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you get three teacups\Nfrom that cabinet over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.19,0:09:02.74,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Is three enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.74,0:09:05.90,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,I have this cup I'm using.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.96,0:09:09.91,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Did you buy new cups?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.91,0:09:12.15,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure we should use these?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:18.34,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They just look new because I clean\Nthem with baking soda after each use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.34,0:09:20.79,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're so precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.79,0:09:23.04,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,I even bought lemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.03,0:09:26.79,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I see you still like lemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.43,0:09:30.59,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if we use\Nthe teabags we brought?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.59,0:09:33.81,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I already have so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.65,0:09:38.12,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we compare a few teas?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.12,0:09:39.44,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.44,0:09:42.23,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is a real ladies' party.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:45.18,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose we can celebrate\Nyour hospital discharge early.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:50.56,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Your wife suddenly developed appendicitis?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:53.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I shouldn't have worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.71,0:09:56.98,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,But you shouldn't make light of appendicitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.98,0:09:58.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.70,0:10:01.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could he be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.10,0:10:07.17,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,These photos brings back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.17,0:10:08.92,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,It's from the school festival!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.14,0:10:12.57,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you keep all your old\Nphotos on your phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.57,0:10:15.05,DCMain,JURII,0000,0000,0000,,Only the ones I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.32,0:10:18.44,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it this school festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.44,0:10:21.55,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,When Reina got Sosaki-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.83,0:10:23.75,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Sosaki-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:26.72,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,The most popular boy in our class.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.72,0:10:28.31,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:32.40,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Reina-san, you're so lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.15,0:10:34.94,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.36,0:10:39.74,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,The other day I nearly\Nlost a fortune in stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.03,0:10:43.99,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,My husband's just a nouveau riche.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.30,0:10:48.50,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought my son had a simple cold during\Nhis exams, but it turned out to be the flu.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:51.58,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was ruined because\Nwe didn't notice in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:55.14,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm walking on a tightrope.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.14,0:10:57.76,DCMain,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,One wrong step, and I'll be at rock bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:14.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did that scream come from this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:15.76,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.14,0:11:18.74,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.00,0:11:24.19,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Reina?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.19,0:11:25.50,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Reina!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:36.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe someone was poisoned at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:40.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,By the time the doctor arrived, it was already too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.19,0:11:43.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.56,0:11:46.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Haido resident Suto Reina,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.91,0:11:48.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Forty-two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.64,0:11:51.88,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Today, she came to the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.88,0:11:57.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,with two of her high school\Nclassmates to see Kosaka Juri,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.15,0:11:59.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,another one of her classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.19,0:12:04.66,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Suto-san arrived before her other two friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.88,0:12:11.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The cause of death seems to be\Nasphyxiation caused by cyanide poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.32,0:12:12.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.40,0:12:16.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But why was she drinking tea at a hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.31,0:12:20.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The patient Kosaka-san liked tea,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.64,0:12:24.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and they always held tea parties\Nwhen the four of them got together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.92,0:12:25.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:32.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means those three had the\Nopportunity to poison the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:38.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But the victim drank several cups\Nof tea without any problem
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.60,0:12:40.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,when she suddenly seemed to be in pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.76,0:12:41.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:46.38,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible she had been made to\Nswallow a poison capsule beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:50.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's possible the crime\Nwasn't committed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.76,0:12:53.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.66,0:12:54.46,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:55.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.93,0:13:00.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The phone dropped over here\Nhad lots of pictures on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.10,0:13:03.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but the dead lady has\Nchopsticks in her right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.55,0:13:06.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.80,0:13:10.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just touch things at a crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.05,0:13:13.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What's strange about it, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.32,0:13:14.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's normal for people to hold\Nchopsticks in their right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.99,0:13:17.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the cup that broke on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.87,0:13:19.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.66,0:13:24.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's lipstick on the right side of the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.10,0:13:29.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean she was\Ndrinking tea with her left hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.80,0:13:31.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:35.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But why did the victim use her left hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.73,0:13:38.60,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It's because she had\Nsomething in her right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:45.67,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,For example, she may have been\Nlooking at pictures on her phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.16,0:13:47.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Pictures on...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.78,0:13:48.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,...her phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.22,0:13:50.25,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.25,0:13:54.73,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,When people focus on one\Nthing, they ignore all others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.73,0:13:58.43,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the position of the cup\Nor its handle were changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.43,0:14:00.42,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,she would pick it up without noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:05.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit must have used this tendency\Nto make the victim drink the poison
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.70,0:14:10.20,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,by switching their own\Npoisoned cup with the victim's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:12.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Switching them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.45,0:14:16.42,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.42,0:14:21.64,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Putting poison in your own cup and\Nswitching it with the victim's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.64,0:14:23.67,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,is safer than directly\Npoisoning the victim's cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.46,0:14:27.86,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,No one seemed to be using saucers,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.86,0:14:30.18,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,so it would be easy to\Nadjust the cups' positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.60,0:14:32.60,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Mori-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.60,0:14:34.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:37.73,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This detective again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.92,0:14:40.49,DCMain,KATSUKII,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's no way we could switch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.49,0:14:43.12,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Only her tea had lemon slices in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.12,0:14:47.19,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,And look closely at the\Ncolor of everyone's tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:48.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The color?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.88,0:14:54.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All three are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.22,0:14:57.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,From right to left, there's\Nbrown, blue, and yellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.81,0:15:02.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was drinking a reddish tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:05.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't get these teas confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.07,0:15:09.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, if someone poisoned the tea,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:13.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,there must be a container or\Nbag used to contain the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.25,0:15:18.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe a thorough search of the\Nroom will turn up something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.70,0:15:19.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.63,0:15:23.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit may still have\Nit on their person, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.91,0:15:29.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,After we search the three of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.52,0:15:33.28,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,we'll question you separately\Nin another room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:35.28,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.03,0:15:40.54,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.10,0:15:44.29,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.68,0:15:47.36,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,I made everyone's tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:51.80,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, they were my guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.14,0:15:58.25,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,But all I did was put the tea\Nbags in cups and add water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.25,0:16:01.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the only one who touched the cups?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:03.20,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.20,0:16:08.32,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Happo-san and Beppu-san got\Nthe cups out of the cupboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.64,0:16:14.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it would make sense to\Nfind everyone's fingerprints on the cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.63,0:16:18.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you make so\Nmany different kinds of tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.33,0:16:20.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Normally you only use one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.61,0:16:26.63,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knows I like herb tea, so\NI had received quite a few as gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:29.61,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Happo-san brought some as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.61,0:16:32.57,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we could compare teas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:33.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.23,0:16:40.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As the person who suggested you compare\Nteas and then made the tea,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.48,0:16:45.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,it was easiest for you to poison the tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.52,0:16:47.81,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,I-I didn't do anything like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.23,0:16:51.41,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone saw me pour the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:56.32,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,and Suto-san drank nearly half \Nher tea before she collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.65,0:16:59.32,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, as I told you before,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.32,0:17:03.26,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,she would have noticed immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.26,0:17:05.88,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,if I had switched my\Npoisoned cup with hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.88,0:17:07.83,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.02,0:17:13.38,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,I was drinking a blue herb\Ntea called "Butterfly Tea."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:17.84,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,She would have noticed\Nif I had switched ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.04,0:17:24.10,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Suto-san was drinking a red\Nherb tea called "Hibiscus Tea."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.41,0:17:28.69,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the\Nother two were drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:30.37,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.37,0:17:34.55,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,Happo-san was drinking a brown\Nherb tea called "Peppermint,"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:38.95,DCMain,JURI,0000,0000,0000,,and Beppu-san was drinking a\Nyellow herb tea called "Chamomile."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:45.20,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I was drinking Peppermint.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.74,0:17:47.76,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would be green,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.76,0:17:51.00,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,but I was disappointed\Nwhen I saw it was brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:54.09,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,You know, because of the\Ncolor "peppermint green."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.64,0:17:58.55,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Juri, who knows more about\Ntea than I do, was giggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.96,0:18:02.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But red and brown look pretty similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.59,0:18:04.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It would've been easiest for you to switchâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:06.56,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,They look nothing alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.92,0:18:09.39,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Mine was a common brown,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.39,0:18:12.16,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,but Reina's was a garish red!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.16,0:18:14.19,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Surely she couldn't have confused these!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.67,0:18:18.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Did everyone choose their own tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:19.73,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.73,0:18:22.20,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,We lined them up on the table\Nand chose what we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.60,0:18:25.39,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Once we finished drinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.39,0:18:27.40,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,we wiped the cups with\Ntissues for our next cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.40,0:18:32.21,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Juri had been drinking a\Nblue tea before we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.46,0:18:35.71,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,She said it was healthy but bitter,\Nso she didn't recommend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.03,0:18:38.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How were the four of you seated?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.81,0:18:40.08,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.08,0:18:45.92,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Clockwise it was me, Reina,\NKatsuki, and Juri, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.31,0:18:48.60,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuki and I looked from\Neither side of Reina
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.60,0:18:52.73,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,at the cell phone pictures\Nshe was looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.50,0:18:56.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Who suggested you look at the photos?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.48,0:18:57.61,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.04,0:19:00.92,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently Juri had shown\Nthem to her before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.92,0:19:05.13,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to show everyone\Nthe next time we visited.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.13,0:19:08.74,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,But Reina wouldn't let go of her phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.74,0:19:11.62,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuki and I had to look over her shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.99,0:19:16.30,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,She's always been that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.30,0:19:20.27,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,She's possessive, self-absorbed,\Nand indifferent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:23.24,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Her current husband is my ex-boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.24,0:19:25.93,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,She took him from me.\NShe took him from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.74,0:19:31.78,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I didn't want to hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.81,0:19:34.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.11,0:19:38.07,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuki probably hated her more than I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.14,0:19:42.52,DCMain,TOKIE,0000,0000,0000,,She was upset about the heavy\Nloss she suffered because of Reina.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:43.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy loss?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:48.33,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I was upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:51.70,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The stock Reina recommended\Nto me crashed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.70,0:19:53.46,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I nearly lost a fortune,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.99,0:19:58.05,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but Reina made a killing selling\Nall her stock before it dropped!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:20:01.22,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You have our sympathies...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.22,0:20:04.00,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm drowning in debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.00,0:20:07.21,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,She could've told me if she\Nknew it was going to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.71,0:20:09.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is that why you killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.33,0:20:13.85,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If that would've brought my money\Nback, I might have considered it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.31,0:20:21.04,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to speak ill of the dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.04,0:20:24.74,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but I think Juri may have hated her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.14,0:20:30.04,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Juri's son failed his entrance\Nexam because of Reina.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.36,0:20:32.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, failed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.71,0:20:36.46,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Juri and Reina's children are classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:39.07,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,They were trying to get into\Nthe same middle school,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.07,0:20:42.55,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but Reina's son, who came over to\Nstudy the day before the exam,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:44.32,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,was sick with the flu.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.32,0:20:46.61,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Juri's son got it from him,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.61,0:20:49.18,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,and he didn't have time to worry\Nabout the entrance exam anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:52.80,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You have our sympathies...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.32,0:20:58.31,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Juri seemed so optimistic about\Nthe results before the exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.32,0:21:07.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, everyone\Nhad motive to kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:08.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.61,0:21:09.95,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.19,0:21:13.30,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,None of us would ever do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.63,0:21:16.75,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We all resented her,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:22.59,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but Reina had always been that\Nway, so we just dealt with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.87,0:21:25.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.31,0:21:30.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone leave the room once\Nyou started drinking tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.47,0:21:31.85,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:35.60,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Tokie and I each left once separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.83,0:21:37.52,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.52,0:21:40.37,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Tokie went to buy snacks for the tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.37,0:21:43.97,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Juri and Reina were\Nin the room the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.97,0:21:47.35,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Reina went to get hot water,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.35,0:21:51.12,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but that was before Tokie and I arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.14,0:21:54.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.91,0:21:57.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When did youâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.09,0:21:59.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do those tea cups belong to the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.71,0:22:02.76,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, those are Juri's cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.76,0:22:06.51,DCMain,KATSUKI,0000,0000,0000,,She said she keeps them sparkling\Nclean with baking soda.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.06,0:22:14.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That means she's the only one who\Ncould have poisoned the victim's tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.12,0:22:21.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The question is how did she make\Nthe victim pick up the cup?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:23:57.37,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:47.53,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,The lip of the teacup?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.07,0:23:50.44,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone put poison there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.88,0:23:53.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit must have been pretty bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.24,0:23:54.16,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.56,0:23:57.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:24:00.24,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Only one person could have applied poison
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.24,0:24:05.46,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,to their own cup and watched for an\Nopportunity to switch it with the victim's.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.19,0:24:08.96,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.49,0:24:13.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is\N"The Tense Tea Party, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.49,0:24:13.64,DCNextEp,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Tense Tea Party\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Lemons
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.35,0:24:32.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.65,0:24:34.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Lemons!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:40.03,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.19,0:24:36.59,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Lemons remind me of Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.59,0:24:37.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.21,0:24:38.53,DCMain,AMURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He must be a sour man.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.53,0:24:39.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}No, I'm not.
